12.13	Confirmation_(Lutheran_Church)	Confirmation (Lutheran Church)	Confirmation in the Lutheran Church is a public profession of faith prepared for by long and careful instruction. In English, it is called "affirmation of baptism", and is a mature and public profession of the faith which "marks the completion of the congregation's program of confirmation ministry".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9e/LutheranClergy.JPG/220px-LutheranClergy.JPG
